year sales growth of Lloyds Banking Group plc (LYG) stands at -8.78 while the industry's and the sector's growth for next 5 years ticked at 14.25 and 14.36 respectively. The stock exchanged hands 1.95 Million shares versus average trading capacity of 4.93 Million shares, yielding a market cap of $62.54 Billion. The Company's main business activities are retail and commercial banking, general insurance, and long-term savings, protection and investment. The stock has 5 year expected PEG ratio of 0 whereas its trailing twelve month P/E ratio is 20.45. The Company operates through three segments: UK Private Banking (Arbuthnot Latham & Co, Limited), Retail Banking and Group Centre.Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with our FREE daily email newsletter.

 




