Analysts Set Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) Price Target at $72.83
21 July 2017



Among 13 analysts covering Lloyds Banking (NYSE:LYG), 4 have Buy rating, 6 Sell and 3 Hold. Six investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, two have issued a hold rating and ten have given a buy rating to the company's stock.COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: "Morgan Stanley Analysts Give Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) a GBX 85 Price Target" was posted by Transcript Daily and is owned by of Transcript Daily.LYG has been the topic of several research analyst reports.


Derailed train in Brooklyn affecting B, Q service
Southbound Q Subway trains are running on the N Subway line from Atlantic Avenue to Barclays Center to Coney Island-Stillwell Ave. As many as 34 people were hurt when two subway cars of the A train derailed at the bustling 125th Street station on June 27.
The current consensus rating on Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) is Buy (Score: 2.50) with a consensus target price of GBX 74.88 per share, a potential. Berenberg Bank cut Lloyds Banking Group PLC to a sell rating and set a GBX 55 ($0.72) target price for the company.in a report on Monday, March 27th. The stock of Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) has "Buy" rating given on Thursday, February 4 by HSBC. UBS AG set a GBX 85 ($1.11) target price on Lloyds Banking Group PLC and gave the stock a "buy" rating in a research note on Monday, July 10th.Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LLOY) opened at 67.20 on Monday. 2,556,159 shares of the company's stock traded hands. Lloyds Banking Group PLC has a 1-year low of GBX 50.68 and a 1-year high of GBX 73.58. The stock has a 50-day moving average of $3.64 and a 200 day moving average of $3.43. The company's market capitalization is GBX 54.50 billion. Lloyds Banking Group PLC has GBX 108 highest and GBX 48 lowest target. If you are reading this article on another publication, it was copied illegally and reposted in violation of United States & global copyright and trademark legislation. The correct version of this news story can be accessed at https://www.thecerbatgem.com/2017/07/21/deutsche-bank-ag-reiterates-buy-rating-for-lloyds-banking-group-plc-lonlloy-updated.html.A number of institutional investors have recently bought and sold shares of the company. Insiders bought 55,580 shares of company stock worth $3,975,500 in the last 90 days.
