Home / Investing / Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) has been reiterated  to Sell in a statement by Citigroup earlier today.

Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) has been reiterated  to Sell in a statement by Citigroup earlier today.


By Al Wild


Updated: July 20, 2017




Citigroup has reiterated Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY)  to Sell in a statement released on 07/21/2017.  
On Wednesday July 19, 2017, Exane BNP Paribas released a statement on Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) maintained the target price at 63.00GBX that suggested a downside of -0.06%.
Boasting a price of 68.43GBX, Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY) traded -0.54% lower on the day. With the last close up 1.48% from the two hundred day average, compared with the S&P 500 Index which has increased 0.07% over the date range.  Lloyds Banking Group PLC has recorded a 50-day average of 67.65GBX and a two hundred day average of 67.32GBX.  Volume of trade was down over the average, with 6,202,457 shares of LLOY changing hands under the typical 182,775,008 
Performance Chart

With a total market value of 0 GBX, Lloyds Banking Group PLC has price-earnings ratio of 22.77 with a one year low of 50.68GBX and a one year high of 73.58GBX .
A total of 21 analysts have released a research note on LLOY.  Five analysts rating the company a strong buy, fourteen analysts rating the company a buy, five analysts rating the company a hold, two analysts rating the company a underperform, and finally one analyst rating the company a sell with a one year target of 69.90GBX.
More About Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LON:LLOY)
Lloyds Banking Group plc is a provider of financial services to individual and business customers in the United Kingdom. The Company's main business activities are retail and commercial banking, general insurance, and long-term savings, protection and investment. The Company's segments are Retail, Commercial Banking, Consumer Finance, Insurance and Other. The Retail segment offers a range of financial service products, including current accounts, savings and mortgages. The Commercial Banking segment offers a range of products and services, such as lending, transactional banking, working capital management, risk management and debt capital markets services. The Consumer Finance segment offers consumer lending products, including motor finance, credit cards, and unsecured personal loans. The Insurance segment provides a range of protection, pension and investment products. Its brands include Lloyds Bank, Halifax, Bank of Scotland, Scottish Widows, Colleys, Lex Autolease and AMC.

